source.note: Article XV, sections 20 to 24, of the Constitution of Nebraska, as adopted in 1992 by Initiative 407, and in 1994 by Initiative 408, have been omitted because of the decisions of the Nebraska Supreme Court in Duggan v. Beermann, 245 Neb. 907, 515 N.W.2d 788 (1994) and Duggan v. Beermann, 249 Neb. 411, 544 N.W.2d 68 (1996).
